    "causal_summary": "Phase 018 shipped executor selection with two kinds: `native` (default) and `cli-codex` (new). Three more kinds were reserved in the enum (`cli-copilot`, `cli-gemini`, `cli-claude-code`) but rejected at config load with `ExecutorNotWiredError`. This packet wires all three. Both iterative skills (sk-deep-research + sk-deep-review) gain support for four CLI executors plus native. Each CLI has a different invocation surface, so `executor-config.ts` grows per-kind flag-compatibility validation. Cross-CLI delegation is documented: any CLI executor CAN, in theory, invoke the other CLI skills from within its iteration via its shell/sandbox, with the anti-pattern being self-recursive invocation.",
